<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend Framework by default uses URL paths to encode module/controller/action/parameters. Good!</p>

<p>Parameters values are urlencoded by default ("?" =&gt; "%3f", "/" =&gt; "%2f", etc.). Good!</p>

<p>Apache by default disallows encoded slashes (%2f) in URL path parts and issues a "fake" 404 not found message, even when using mod_rewrite and everything is set up correctly. BAD!</p>

<p>This "feature" can be disabled using the "AllowEncodedSlashes On" directive, but unfortunately it has to be done on a server-wide or virtualhost level.</p>

<p>I'm surprised that this hasn't been included in documentation as it affects anyone using the default ZF router and a default Apache install who tries to pass slashes via GET.</p>

<p>References:
 <a href="http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.0/mod/core.html#allowencodedslashes">http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.0/…</a></p>

